This paper deals with reinforcement learning algorithms, which are commonly studied in the machine learning community. The paper specifically focuses on the stability of these algorithms with nonlinear function approximation, which falls under the category of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.RO (Robotics).
